    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-11-25T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-11-25T22:00:00-05:00" n="1261"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1261">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Stokes, William N.: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Peiping</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clubb</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-11-26T11:00:00+08:00"
                            >November 26, 1949—11 a. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 25—11:33 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2096. Ward informed me this morning Stokes had been taken court 9 a. m. without
                    warrant for hearing re “spying charges” which Ward connected with June 21
                        report<note n="79" xml:id="d1261fn79">For information on Communist “spy
                        ring” charges, see telegram No. 1039, June 19, from the Consul General at
                        Peiping, <ref target="#pg_965">p. 965</ref>.</note> but whether as accused
                    or witness or in other capacity unindicated to Americans. Ward was refused
                    permission accompany.</p>
                <p>Will phone Mukden each schedule until Stokes returns.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 2096; Department pass Shanghai 1219, Nanking 1178, Tientsin
                    102.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clubb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
